Detailed Description

The request data for searches. This is the data that can be set for a search.

Constructor & Destructor Documentation

WFAPI::OneSearchQuery::OneSearchQuery ( const WFString &  what,
const WGS84Coordinate &  position,
SearchType  searchType = SEARCH_FOR_EVERYTHING,
wf_int32  round = WF_MAX_INT32 
)

Constructor. Use this constructor when searching for a string around the users position (which you provide).

Typically you need this when using LBS system to get the users coordinate, and the user wants to search for a specific street or object around him.

Parameters:
what What to Search for.
position Search hits will be sorted around this position.
searchType What type of search this is. Possible values are "address" and "all". The type "address" is intended for use with round 0.
round The round to search in, round 0 means that the search will be done only in internal databases, round 1 means that the search will be done in third party directories only. If set to WF_MAX_INT32 the search will be done in all directories.

Constructor. Use this constructor when making a search for what, where and country (TopRegionID). Use this when you want to search for things around some arbitrary adress rather than a position. This will search in all possible categories.

Parameters:
what What to Search for.
where Used to limit the search hits to those in matching areas (City or area).
topRegionID In what region/country/state to search in.
searchType What type of search this is. Possible values are "address" and "all". The type "address" is intended for use with round 0.
round The round to search in, round 0 means that the search will be done only in internal databases, round 1 means that the search will be done in third party directories only. If set to WF_MAX_INT32 the search will be done in all directories.

Constructor. Use this constructor when making a search for what, where and country (TopRegionID). Use this when you want to search for things around some arbitrary adress rather than a position. This will search in the categories you specify.

Parameters:
what What to Search for.
where Used to limit the search hits to those in matching areas (City or area).
topRegionID In what region/country/state to search in.
categoryIDs One or more specific categories to search in.
searchType What type of search this is. Possible values are "address" and "all". The type "address" is intended for use with round 0.
round The round to search in, round 0 means that the search will be done only in internal databases, round 1 means that the search will be done in third party directories only. If set to WF_MAX_INT32 the search will be done in all directories.

WFAPI::OneSearchQuery::OneSearchQuery ( const WFString &  what,
const WFString &  where,
std::vector< wf_int32 >  categoryIDs,
const WGS84Coordinate &  position,

wf_uint32  topRegionID,
SearchType  searchType = SEARCH_FOR_EVERYTHING,
wf_int32  maxHits = DEFAULT_MAX_SEARCH_HITS,
wf_int32  round = WF_MAX_INT32,
SearchSorting  searchSorting = DISTANCE_SORT,
bool  includeInfoFields = true 
)

Constructor. Use this constructor if you really know what you are doing, and have very specific needs that the above constructors cannot fulfill.

Warning: The location where the search should be performed is specified by either using parameter ("position"), or ("where" and "topRegionID"). Exactly one of these two combinations must be used.

Parameters:
what What to Search for. Can be an empty string.
where Used to limit the search hits to those in matching areas (City or area). Can be an empty string.
categoryIDs The category to search within instead of search using a string. Use WF_MAX_UINT32 if not to search by categoryIDs.
position The position to find matches around. Ignored if set to (180,180)
radius The maximum distance from the position to find matches To ignore this value, set it to 0.
topRegionID In what region/country/state to search. Pass an empty list to ignore this parameter.
maxHits The maximum number of hits wanted.
round The round to search in, round 0 means that the search will be done only in internal databases, round 1 means that the search will be done in third party directories only. If set to WF_MAX_INT32 the search will be done in all directories.
searchSorting In what order to return the matches, see SearchSorting enumeration.
includeInfoFields set if to include InfoItems in each search result item
searchType What type of search this is. Possible values are "address" and "all". The type "address" is intended for use with round 0.
